"""h5cve -- a thin CVE-case orchestrator.

Investigating a malformed-input CVE means chaining the same tools by hand:
h5policy for the decision, h5markers/h5explain to navigate, the exact-build probe
to check safe rejection, the registry to name the invariant.  h5cve chains them
into one provenance-stamped case bundle and auto-populates the cve-case.yml
schema.  It DUPLICATES none of them -- it shells out and collects.

  h5cve init  <id> --poc FILE     new bundle: PoC, sha256, skeleton case.yml
  h5cve triage <case>             h5policy (forensic+strict), markers, explain;
                                  map the primary finding -> invariant/scope/record
  h5cve verify <case> --baseline BINDIR [--candidate BINDIR]
                                  exact-build probe(s): safe reject + no activation
  h5cve minimize <case>           [deferred: reducer is roadmap change #5]
  h5cve variants <case>           [deferred: mutator is roadmap change #5]
  h5cve promote <case>            emit tests expectation + curated registry case

A bundle is a directory under cases/<id>/ holding case.yml plus the collected
artifacts (h5policy-forensic.json, h5policy-strict.json, markers.json,
explain-transcript.txt, baseline/candidate-result.json, tool-and-build-
provenance.json).  cases/ is working scratch; `promote` is what lands tracked
artifacts in tests/ and registry/.
"""
